cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.SE, cs.HC

The paper discusses the use of Physically Unclonable Functions (PUFs) for generating unique and secure keys in low-cost cryptographic applications. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the use of DRAM for PUFs, which falls under the category of electronic technology (cs.ET). The methodology proposed in the paper is fast and robust, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
